#. <section class="sutta" id="an5.135"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an5.135:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 5"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an5.135:0.2"
msgid "14. Rājavagga"
msgstr "14. Kings"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an5.135:0.3"
msgid "135. Paṭhamapatthanāsutta"
msgstr "135. Aspiration (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an5.135:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Pañcahi, bhikkhave, aṅgehi samannāgato rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa "
"jeṭṭho putto rajjaṃ pattheti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, an anointed aristocratic king’s eldest son with five factors "
"aspires to kingship."

msgctxt "an5.135:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.135:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa jeṭṭho putto ubhato "
"sujāto hoti mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā "
"pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when an anointed aristocratic king’s eldest son is well born on both "
"his mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, irrefutable and impeccable "
"in questions of ancestry back to the seventh paternal generation."

msgctxt "an5.135:1.4"
msgid ""
"abhirūpo hoti dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya samannāgato;"
msgstr "He is attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty."

msgctxt "an5.135:1.5"
msgid "mātāpitūnaṃ piyo hoti manāpo;"
msgstr "He is dear and beloved to his parents."

msgctxt "an5.135:1.6"
msgid "negamajānapadassa piyo hoti manāpo;"
msgstr "He is dear and beloved to the people of town and country."

msgctxt "an5.135:1.7"
msgid ""
"yāni tāni raññaṃ khattiyānaṃ muddhāvasittānaṃ sippaṭṭhānāni hatthismiṃ vā "
"assasmiṃ vā rathasmiṃ vā dhanusmiṃ vā tharusmiṃ vā tattha sikkhito hoti "
"anavayo."
msgstr ""
"He is trained and skilled in the arts of anointed aristocratic kings, such "
"as elephant riding, horse riding, driving a chariot, archery, and "
"swordsmanship."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.153"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an5.135:2.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "He thinks:"

msgctxt "an5.135:2.2"
msgid ""
"‘ahaṃ khomhi ubhato sujāto mātito ca pitito ca, saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva "
"sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakkuṭṭho jātivādena."
msgstr ""
"‘I’m well born on both my mother’s and father’s side, of pure descent, "
"irrefutable and impeccable in questions of ancestry back to the seventh "
"paternal generation."

msgctxt "an5.135:2.3"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ rajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr "Why shouldn’t I aspire to kingship?"

msgctxt "an5.135:2.4"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ khomhi abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko paramāya vaṇṇapokkharatāya "
"samannāgato."
msgstr "I’m attractive, good-looking, lovely, of surpassing beauty."

msgctxt "an5.135:2.5"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ rajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr "Why shouldn’t I aspire to kingship?"

msgctxt "an5.135:2.6"
msgid "Ahaṃ khomhi mātāpitūnaṃ piyo manāpo."
msgstr "I’m dear and beloved to my parents."

msgctxt "an5.135:2.7"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ rajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr "Why shouldn’t I aspire to kingship?"

msgctxt "an5.135:2.8"
msgid "Ahaṃ khomhi negamajānapadassa piyo manāpo."
msgstr "I’m dear and beloved to the people of town and country."

msgctxt "an5.135:2.9"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ rajjaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr "Why shouldn’t I aspire to kingship?"

#. VAR: tattha → tatthamhi (bj) | tatthapi (mr)
msgctxt "an5.135:2.10"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ khomhi yāni tāni raññaṃ khattiyānaṃ muddhāvasittānaṃ sippaṭṭhānāni "
"hatthismiṃ vā assasmiṃ vā rathasmiṃ vā dhanusmiṃ vā tharusmiṃ vā, tattha "
"sikkhito anavayo."
msgstr ""
"I’m trained and skilled in the arts of anointed aristocratic kings, such as "
"elephant riding, horse riding, driving a chariot, archery, and swordsmanship."

msgctxt "an5.135:2.11"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ rajjaṃ na pattheyyan’ti."
msgstr "Why shouldn’t I aspire to kingship?’"

msgctxt "an5.135:2.12"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi aṅgehi samannāgato rañño khattiyassa "
"muddhāvasittassa jeṭṭho putto rajjaṃ pattheti."
msgstr ""
"An anointed aristocratic king’s eldest son with these five factors aspires "
"to kingship."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an5.135:3.1"
msgid ""
"Evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āsavānaṃ "
"khayaṃ pattheti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant with five qualities aspires to end the "
"defilements."

msgctxt "an5.135:3.2"
msgid "Katamehi pañcahi?"
msgstr "What five?"

msgctxt "an5.135:3.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu saddho hoti, saddahati tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:"
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant has faith in the Realized One’s awakening:"

msgctxt "an5.135:3.4"
msgid ""
"‘itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno sugato lokavidū "
"anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho bhagavā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘That Blessed One is perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, accomplished in "
"knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme guide for those "
"who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, blessed.’"

msgctxt "an5.135:3.5"
msgid ""
"Appābādho hoti appātaṅko, samavepākiniyā gahaṇiyā samannāgato nātisītāya "
"nāccuṇhāya majjhimāya padhānakkhamāya;"
msgstr ""
"They are rarely ill or unwell. Their stomach digests well, being neither too "
"hot nor too cold, but just right, and fit for meditation."

msgctxt "an5.135:3.6"
msgid ""
"asaṭho hoti amāyāvī, yathābhūtaṃ attānaṃ āvikattā satthari vā viññūsu vā "
"sabrahmacārīsu;"
msgstr ""
"They’re not devious or deceitful. They reveal themselves honestly to the "
"Teacher or sensible spiritual companions."

msgctxt "an5.135:3.7"
msgid ""
"āraddhavīriyo viharati akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ "
"upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu dhammesu;"
msgstr ""
"They live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and "
"gaining skillful qualities. They’re strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking "
"off when it comes to developing skillful qualities."

msgctxt "an5.135:3.8"
msgid ""
"paññavā hoti udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya nibbedhikāya "
"sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"They’re wise. They have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is "
"noble, penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.154"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an5.135:4.1"
msgid "Tassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "They think:"

msgctxt "an5.135:4.2"
msgid "‘ahaṃ khomhi saddho, saddahāmi tathāgatassa bodhiṃ:"
msgstr "‘I am a person of faith; I have faith in the Realized One’s awakening …"

msgctxt "an5.135:4.3"
msgid ""
"“itipi so bhagavā arahaṃ sammāsambuddho … pe … satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho "
"bhagavā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an5.135:4.4"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr "Why shouldn’t I aspire to end the defilements?"

msgctxt "an5.135:4.5"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ khomhi appābādho appātaṅko samavepākiniyā gahaṇiyā samannāgato "
"nātisītāya nāccuṇhāya majjhimāya padhānakkhamāya."
msgstr ""
"I’m rarely ill or unwell. My stomach digests well, being neither too hot nor "
"too cold, but just right, and fit for meditation."

msgctxt "an5.135:4.6"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr "Why shouldn’t I aspire to end the defilements?"

msgctxt "an5.135:4.7"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ khomhi asaṭho amāyāvī yathābhūtaṃ attānaṃ āvikattā satthari vā viññūsu "
"vā sabrahmacārīsu."
msgstr ""
"I reveal myself honestly to the Teacher or sensible spiritual companions."

msgctxt "an5.135:4.8"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr "Why shouldn’t I aspire to end the defilements?"

msgctxt "an5.135:4.9"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ khomhi āraddhavīriyo viharāmi akusalānaṃ dhammānaṃ pahānāya, kusalānaṃ "
"dhammānaṃ upasampadāya, thāmavā daḷhaparakkamo anikkhittadhuro kusalesu "
"dhammesu."
msgstr ""
"I live with energy roused up for giving up unskillful qualities and gaining "
"skillful qualities. I’m strong, staunchly vigorous, not slacking off when it "
"comes to developing skillful qualities."

msgctxt "an5.135:4.10"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyaṃ."
msgstr "Why shouldn’t I aspire to end the defilements?"

msgctxt "an5.135:4.11"
msgid ""
"Ahaṃ khomhi paññavā udayatthagāminiyā paññāya samannāgato ariyāya "
"nibbedhikāya sammā dukkhakkhayagāminiyā."
msgstr ""
"I’m wise. I have the wisdom of arising and passing away which is noble, "
"penetrative, and leads to the complete ending of suffering."

msgctxt "an5.135:4.12"
msgid "Kasmāhaṃ āsavānaṃ khayaṃ na pattheyyan’ti."
msgstr "Why shouldn’t I aspire to end the defilements?’"

msgctxt "an5.135:4.13"
msgid ""
"Imehi kho, bhikkhave, pañcahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āsavānaṃ khayaṃ "
"patthetī”ti."
msgstr "A mendicant with these five qualities aspires to end the defilements.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an5.135:4.14"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
